metadata.description: U.S. individual income percentiles by age and year
metadata.source: Census Bureau CPS ASEC via IPUMS-CPS

methodology.income_exclusions: NIU, missing, zero, and negative values excluded

metadata.citation: Sarah Flood, Miriam King, Renae Rodgers, Steven Ruggles, J. Robert Warren, et al. IPUMS CPS: Version 13.0 [dataset]. Minneapolis, MN: IPUMS, 2025. https://doi.org/10.18128/D030.V13.0

after_tax_model.description: Estimated after-tax income using simplified tax model

components.federal: Actual single-filer brackets + standard deduction + personal exemption by year (1961-2025)
components.fica: Employee share: SS (year-specific rate to wage base, 4.2% in 2011-12) + Medicare (year-specific, 0% pre-1966, 1.45% from 1986+) + Addl Medicare (0.9% >$200k, 2013+)
components.state: Flat 5.0% effective rate on (income - std deduction) as population-weighted average

assumptions: Single filer with standard deduction (no itemizing)
FICA applied to total income (overstates for those with significant non-wage income)
No tax credits (EITC, child credit, etc.) — understates after-tax income for lower brackets
State tax is a national average; actual varies ~0-13% by state
After-tax percentiles are exact; after-tax mean is approximate
Pre-1994: Medicare capped at SS wage base; 1994+: uncapped
